#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool.md:1
msgid "Added new class to manually create a Cocoa NSAutoreleasePool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool.md:3
msgid ""
"The new class vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool allows manually creating and draining "
"a Cocoa autorelease pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool.md:5
msgid ""
"The Cocoa event loop creates an NSAutoreleasePool at the beginning of every "
"cycle of an event loop, and drains it at the end. But if you do lots of "
"things before the end of the event loop, memory usage can temporarily grow "
"high."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool.md:7
msgid ""
"This class can be useful in scenarios where a loop creates, initializes, and "
"then deletes a vtkCocoaRenderWindow, which doesn't yield back to the Cocoa "
"event loop. Memory usage will thus increase with every iteration of such a "
"loop. The memory will eventually be reclaimed (so there's no leak in that "
"sense), but using this class allows manual control over that, reducing the "
"high water mark of memory usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-vtkCocoaAutoreleasePool.md:9
msgid ""
"Other operating systems work differently, and so this class is only for "
"macOS."
msgstr ""
